The paper deals with the task of Semantic Image Interpretation (SII), which involves extracting structured semantic descriptions from images. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes the use of Logic Tensor Networks (LTNs), which integrate neural networks with first-order fuzzy logic, to improve the performance of SII tasks. This makes it likely that the paper would also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of logical constraints to improve the robustness of the learning system, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
